    <p class="govuk-body">
      To enable the recovery partition, log out as a local user and log in as the administrator.
    </p>

    <h3 class="govuk-heading-m">
      Administrator login details
    </h3>

    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>Username: .\localadmin</li>
      <li>Password: The admin user password retrieved through <%= govuk_link_to 'step 2 of this guide', devices_guide_to_resetting_windows_laptops_and_tablets_get_local_admin_and_bios_passwords_path %></li>
    </ul>

    <p class="govuk-body">Once logged in as administrator, follow the steps below:</p>

    <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
      <li>Open the Windows start menu and type &lsquo;cmd&rsquo; into the search box.</li>
      <li>Right-select on &lsquo;Command prompt&rsquo; and select &lsquo;Run as administrator&rsquo;.</li>
      <li>If asked &lsquo;Do you want to allow this app to make changes to your device?&rsquo;, select &lsquo;Yes&rsquo;.</li>
      <li>Within the command prompt window, type &lsquo;reagentc /enable&rsquo; and press &lsquo;Enter&rsquo; &ndash; after several seconds the output should say &lsquo;Operation Successful&rsquo;.</li>
      <li>Type &lsquo;reagentc /boottore&rsquo; and press &lsquo;Enter&rsquo; &ndash; after several seconds the output should say &lsquo;Operation Successful&rsquo;</li>
      <li>To check the status of the recovery partition, type &lsquo;reagentc /info&rsquo; and press &lsquo;Enter&rsquo; &ndash; after several seconds the output should say &lsquo;Enabled&rsquo;</li>
    </ol>

